h I did once or twice, it was mainly when he was visiting [the area briefly]. And I think he too, tried to get on with his own life, and, perhaps, tried to negotiate things through a lawyer. He was very formal: and if the lawyer said that the mother didn'
t
 want him to be seen because it would be disruptive, he would take the lawyer's word for it, even though lawyers are often very wrong in these circumstances. I'm trying to be sympathetic towards his outlook at that time, but I believe that's largely true,
