\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Peter:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
I was very neighbourly. I got on very well at school. I was lucky, because I was at what's now called a primary school, I was at what was then called an elementary school. I first was in an elementary school in Pimlico. My mother moved from one to another
.
 We went to three different flats, two of them were blown apart, I may say, so it was fortunate we did move in the War. But I went there, well, this was before the War, of course, to Pimlico. I'm talking of subsequently, when we reached the War years, the
se two places were blown down, but I did move, when I was seven, to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceName}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceName}}Belsize{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceType
}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, or Hampstead, and went to an elementary school there, with benches in the classroom, and tiers rising too. There was a famous Miss Sard, she was a grey\_
haired, tall woman, with a bun. And she was a great influence on me, because she believed in my progress, and I did, I certainly did very well in maths and English and other subjects while I was there, and got a few Scholarships at the age of 11. 
I was awarded a Scholarship, for instance, to Christ's Hospital, but I didn't like the yellow socks and the long cloaks. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 So you turned it down yourself, you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Peter:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 Oh no! I think I just said to my mother, you know, that was no place for me! 
And at the time, this was just after the War started, when these various opportunities arose. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceType}}University{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceType}}College{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}, which was the school I went to, was one of the only three schools in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 which remained open during the Blitz, because it had a huge crypt. It was built on a sand\_hill, effectively, and it had a huge crypt, and a lot of the classes proceeded within the crypt. 
\par 
