And going back to what you were saying earlier about the childhood experiences, I remember two things, really, and I think this does sum it up rather. I remember lots of street games. I remember even scoring 500 and something, in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}Belsize Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, with drawn wickets on the brick walls, with two or three friends of mine from around the 
surrounding streets. And I got to know those boys through school, because I certainly was quite a sociable boy, enjoyed school very much, perhaps put more into it, because there wasn't the same number of people around at home. 
