 family, were really the only other relatives that I had. They had one son, a cousin, who I had comparatively little to do with, since he was some seven or eight years older than I was, and really, you know, it wasn't a sort of kind of cousin where you wo
uld have close and familiar associations because you were of similar age, and he'd lived far away too, so we didn't know each other much.
