Moral values? I had two big influences. I've spoken about one of them here, who was my grandmother. She rang true as a bell all her life. I know all of us, sometimes, can think of characters who we, perhaps, elevate more than they even deserve, but 
I think it's true of her, and I don't know of anybody who didn't think the same about her, not only her simplicity but her utter, utter dependability and warmth. And in every respect she was like that. She worked for others all her life. I think, you know
,
 it was a characteristic trait of many women, I mean, in terms of discussing gender inequality, this is a fact about some proportion of women, and she was like that. She worked round the clock. She worked into her sixties, looking after me, for instance, 
a
nd she died at 97. In the last ten years of her life, she lived with me, with my wife and myself, at the time, in the 1960s. And then she used to still ... she was still crocheting, she became rather frail, of course, and lived only at home, but she liked
 her Guinness every morning at 11 o'clock! One Guinness, that was all. And that was her idea of heaven, I think. But she was a very dependable person, and she influenced me in a lot of my attitudes, I'm sure. 
