I can't honestly say that they were. They were, neither of them, versed in instrumental education. My grandmother because she'd never known it, she'd left school at 11, she'd been one of 13, she was the eldest, and she had to look after all the others. 
So her entire life was really slaving after others, and she never got the opportunity to have any education, so she ... and she'd had no real experience of educational institutions. My mother was very much the same, she'd left at 14. She had considerable 
talents. I mean, her level of narrative was really of five\_
star status, in my view, in the way in which she could narrate. And her language was just as vivid as one can imagine. But didn't really feel that she ... she was of the generation who didn't think that they could go back to school, or take a term. 

