Yeah, okay. Religion. The encounter with the Church, let's put it that way, that's an unfair way of putting it, I know, but the truth is that I was not an [adherent] of religion, and an active participant at all, in my childhood, partly because of the wor
king\_class and one\_parent background that I had. But at the age of 16, I discovered it, became an ardent churchgoer every week, on the Sunday, and read avidly about different religions. 
