y. But service in the Army, and trying to do some of the education courses, and teach some of the education courses, took me into an acquaintance with Bertie Russell, and the fact that he was still, in his later years, teaching at Cambridge University, an
d I thought, "Well, why don't I do that?" And the course was then called "Moral Sciences", but it consisted of elements of philosophy, logic, and social psychology and ethics, believe it or not. So those four were pillars of my first two years education. 

