. These were in the War years, remember, and it was a great adventure to cycle all that distance, 30, 40 miles, with a great bag on your back, and we ... it was idyllic, working w
ith other boys of the same age, in a farm, very difficult conditions. The biggest memory was forking dried peas into a barn with a corrugated roof, with the temperature over a hundred in the top of the barn, where I was deputed to be the one to lay it out
 
neatly, right to the top of the corrugated iron. And I did two or three days at that, and every day, every evening, of course, coughed up great clots of black tar from living and working in those conditions. That was a good experience, in the sense of int
roducing me to how some workers managed. So the farming camp was a great experience, and a sociable one at that. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
