But afterwards, after leaving school, in 1946, between July and November, I was looking round for something to do, and answered an advert, whi
ch took me to a private school in Kensington, for, I think it was all of seven of eight weeks before I was called up, where I was a kind of assistant master, exploited, with very little pay, to teach the young faithfuls. And I remember taking them to do p
h
ysical jerks, or physical exercise, in Hyde Park, and being photographed by the Evening Standard, who had a photograph of me doing an astride jump in front of all these little youngsters. And I simply taught them a bit of geography, as far as I remember. 
And that was a tiny experience at a private school, before I went to university, sorry, before I went into the Army. And then went to University in 1948.
