But at the weekend, I drafted this story about what he was reported to have said, and lo and behold, on the Saturday morning ... no, I beg your pardon, the following Monday morning, there was I with my future wife, we were a year awa
y from our marriage, roughly, in these wonderful rooms in St. John's College, just above where Wordsworth used to have rooms, just near the, the Great Hall, or the Hall restaurant, in the First Court, and up the stairs came some steps ... oh, and I was wi
t
h, we were with, Ruth and I were with a friend of mine who'd served in the RAF, and had half his face blown away, he was very disfigured, who was taking a late degree at the University. And there came a knock on the door, and in walked Bertrand Russell. A
nd we thought, "Oh, my God!" We got in all of a fluster! 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
