to the cup! And my friend, who was usually quite conversational, entered a total silence, which he didn't recover from until Bertrand Russell had left. And Bertrand Russell proceeded to give me a scoop, in the sense that not only did he deny the story, bu
t
 he said what really had gone on. And he cared so much about what was thought of him in his native University, that he wanted the error to be put right. So that following week, I not only had the front page headline of my own newspaper, but the story crep
t into a lot of the nationals too, I'm pleased to say. And it was an extraordinary encounter with the great man. And I read quite a bit of his work, of course. 
