e was a man called Fortune, who certainly did make me tick. And he was very much ... there was a man called Meyer Fortes, who was very famous for his work in Africa, in West Africa, Professor Fortes, who breezed in and announced to everybody, at the start
 
of his period of office, that he wasn't going to award any Firsts that following summer, because people couldn't possibly have absorbed enough of him in one year, to have gained from it. He actually said that aloud! But I learned from Fortune, and another
 man [J.C. Trevor] who taught me a bit about the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Caribbean{\*\xmlclose}. And I got to enjoy writing about islands in the Caribbean, particularly the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Virgin Islands{\*\xmlclose}
, and the kind of separate culture. 
