ntil I fell over with dizziness! That kind of idea. And it sticks out very strongly in my mind, those sort of occasions, because it was possible to do that with a wife, in a way that it wouldn't have been possible to do it as just a single student. We wer
e
, in effect, part of the surrounding community, because we lived there. So we did get to know a few people like that, and it was there, incidentally, that I think was where I picked up ... an illness which took me to Addenbrookes Hospital at the end of my
