, it so happens, just behind the Students' Union in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}, not far from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}St. John's{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, because we got to know some of the very poor families who lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname Street}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname address}}Park Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, at that time. But I got caught ill, at the end of my second ye
ar, in the summer, and it was suspected meningitis, and then suspected poliomyelitis, and they never changed that diagnosis, and I was on the danger list for three or four days, I know. And I remember, in the next bed in Addenbrookes, was a man with, a bo
y
