 mental hospital, and put in the only room they had, because it was, you know, War conditions, which just happened to be a padded cell, for a night or two, where I recovered so quickly from this that, literally, the following Saturday, I was back, encoura
ged by this Headmaster, and played in the University Cricket XI that following Saturday after that accident. And that was a kind of symbol. You can argue that it was wrong\_
