rage, or the mode, because in explaining the extreme, it's a challenge to us. And if we're able to explain the extreme, we're probably going further to explain the average than many people allow. Because they themselves make up their minds about what is a
verage, or what is normal, and yet we have historical experiences now, to reveal that some things which we thought were non\_
existent or very rare, are, in fact, extraordinarily common. We're going through that unhappy experience over domestic violence, and 
