\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Peter:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
It was during the period [when] I was in the Army, and trying to make some sort of sense of my life there. It's a curious split 
between, on the one hand, grasping the ... all the mechanics of the internal combustion engine. I think I even said to you that there were 84 lessons, during which I remember, quite distinctly, trying to compose poetry! But it was also at the time when, h
aving got a very good entry to St. Catherine's College, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, for geography ... because I was then interrupted by my compulsory National Service, I began to reflect on what I wanted to make of my life. And one of the interesting points was tha
t I became much more interested both in philosophy, which I subsequently took up at Cambridge, but also politics, I suppose partly because of the mixture of classes that I encountered in the Nissen huts of the battalions that were operating, first in Yeov
il where I went to, then Blandford, and then finally up in Buchanan Castle, near Glasgow. 
