m as a book on social policy. Secondly, Kay, Richard's wife, lived on until ... I'm trying to remember the exact date now. I think it was ... oh, 1990, almost. She lived to 83. She was, she was a few years older than Richard, who was born in 1907, so she 
m
ust have been born about 1904, 3, something like that. She lived to be 86. And in all the years from Richard's death onwards, he devotedly rang her up every Sunday. He'd been very instrumental in helping her, advising her of what to ... about her accommod
ation and other things. 
