d you were having a nice evening together, and somehow, the meal would materialise on the table, but he'd cooked it! And a lot of things he did were almost, almost seemed effortless, on the one hand, but were done with great discretion, on the other. And 
I think this is one reason why he isn't as famous as he ought to be. There was that self\_effacing quality which was partly induced by this homosexuality, I think. He didn't call attention to his strengths, didn't boast about them. 
