ike them. You know, he wasn't trying to presume too much, and he was trying to carry out a kind of organisational job, and he was very effective like that. And I think that in the 1970s, for example, there were a lot of things introduced on disability ben
e
fits which were the fact that they came to pass, was much due to his quiet advocacy, than they were due to, perhaps, some of the efforts that people like David Ennals, as the Secretary of State, and others made. So this cover, as a functionary, I think, w
