But, on the whole, speaking in the round, voluntary Homes were more comfortable. They were more oriented towards the needs of
 the residents. If I say that, as you might appreciate, if you have a residential Home for former university teachers, to get close to home (LAUGHS), for example, you're more likely to have something in common with the other residents. There were certain 
Unions or occupations - medical, the doctors, for example, too - if a Home was organised for such groups, there were sometimes more possibilities of having exchanges, socially, with people. 
