Well, coming back to the private Home, I deliberately went off at a tangent about the voluntary Homes, because they were the most comfortable that we encountered, although some of the local authority converted council homes were 
very close to them in their arrangements, and had certain advantages in some respects, which I could come on to if you want me to. But the private Homes were the most extreme of any that we looked at. We looked at local authority, old Poor Law institution
 type Homes, as well as the new converted, and the purpose\_built ones, and then we looked at the voluntary Homes, which were usually quite small\_scale, I think the average was about 30 or 40 beds in the Home. 
\par But then the private Homes varied. From the ver
y efficiently controlled 30, 40, 50 beds, which was really run for profit for quite rich people, or affluent people, with staff extraordinarily subservient to the patients, or residents. Because these were people who came from rich families or wealthy fam
i
lies, and they had quite a bit of money, the staff were clearly very interested in inheritance, and what these people might leave in their Wills to whom. And yet some of them were, by any standards, comfortable institutions, where the people who had gone 
i
nto them had done so with greater choice. But there were very few in the country, they covered a very tiny percentage of the entire population. But money can buy quite affluent circumstances, and, therefore, we found that, at the top of the range, private
 Homes were, if that is where you wanted to end your days, with your own radio and television set, and different forms of heating and bed\_
warmers and your own mattress, and your own little wardrobe with your valued possessions, mementos of your family, and the photograph of your husband when he was serving in the Great War as a colonel, fine. That was where you could end your days. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
