I think many people doing that kind of research need to understand, as I've gradually learned, that you need almost more time to absorb and write\_up, and get accurate, the various stra
nds of the structural, as well as the descriptive experience - you need more time than you actually take in doing the interviews and going round the Home, and talking to the Chief Welfare Officer, then the Matron, then the Warden, then one or two of the s
taff and so on. 
