And that you have to try to allow for spontaneity: that sometimes one gets chances that will never be repeated, that you need to say, "Hang on a minute, I need to stay with this person for half an hour now. I'm very sorry, but please will 
you postpone the next stage of the timetable". People don't like that, but you have to try to allow for those sort of experiences. I suppose a good plan would be to use a tape\_
recorder, but with discretion, and not overdo it in terms of taking up too much time. 
