asically, residential institutional care was only required for people who needed quite a lot of nursing care at night and in the day, or quite frequent medical supervision, if not treatment. And that providing these in conjunction with, or in relation to 
a scatter of general hospitals, has always seemed to me the right strategy to follow. 
