bviously, raises questions of social services, of what was then the Home Help Service, and how that might be developed more intelligently, but also what would happen to people who, as they got older, found themselves living in very poor physical circumsta
nces, slum dwellings, or dwellings which, for one reason or another, were becoming slums again, and people who were getting to a situation where they needed some help but not a great deal, and the family wasn't always there to be able to do it. 
