nd treatment, but also what social conditions they were in. What kind of food were they receiving? What kind of comforts did they have? Were they, as it were, experiencing conditions which were very acceptable for people in the terminal stage of life? And
 
again, we were worried about this. Although, clearly, some of these institutions were extremely good and extremely - in the estate agents' words, "very well appointed" - there were others which were run in a very skimpy fashion by people who - sometimes o
ne wondered about their history and their quality. So it was quite evident that part of the understanding of what was going on was to check, routinely.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
