developed. The local authorities with the most responsible attitudes to the social services tended to be in urban areas, and they had got the resources and also 
the numbers of people to look at, which meant that, often, procedures were in place to at least perform passably. But some of the places in which the retired elderly were placed, in these nursing Homes, were not exactly very well, or frequently, visited. 
A
