he authorities, the managers, to complete information for you, you really need to see things at first hand in order to know which information is more reliable than other bits of information, and also to begin to observe matters which hadn't occurred to yo
u to ask about when you're sitting in London or in Manchester drafting a questionnaire. So the question of sampling institutions in order to present reliable results is extraordinarily important, and it sounds very ambitious. 
