\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Peter:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
I have a mixture of feelings. On the one hand, I suppose I have to express a certain amount of pride, because it was a very ambitious piece of work, and it was a national study, and it broke new ground in being an enquiry into instituti
ons. Yes, I know that during the great "Blue Book" period of the Victorian times, there were some very informative collections of information from many parishes across the country. Yet much of that was really just putting together different people's accou
n
ts and observations and information, rather than derived by a single team carefully going round and trying, not merely to collect information in a standardised way, but to try to probe it analytically to allow it to be set out, not only a comprehensive wa
y, but also a way which directed attention to the main problems and achievements.
