up complex matters. The complexity often encourages us to believe we've never exhausted the enquiries we should make. 
And there's always more that has to be done. There's more interviewing to be done, there are more references to look up, there are more books to read, there are more visits to be made, and all of that. We tend to fill our diaries so that we're terrificall
y busy. But sooner or later, the thing has to be brought to an end. It has to have a culmination, it has to have a mark. 
