h doctor activities. I'm trying to indicate that it's not just social, it's also using the environment constructively and imaginatively and creatively, to the best possible effect, for the different uses required by the population. Now, if you put it in t
hat way, one can begin to look at the world less in a hierarchical way, and more in an egalitarian way, which I think is extraordinarily important, and very difficult to manage, because we've grown up in such a different spirit. 
