I'm very pleased that the UNDP at least recognised the importance of the idea of absolute poverty applying i
n rich countries as well as poor countries. I think this is the thin end of a very useful intellectual wedge. They actually produced some figures for industrialised countries, whether they're big enough, or reliable enough, or well-researched enough, is a
nother matter. But they've at least produced some figures of the scale of absolute poverty, in a number of high-income and middle-income countries. 
