ry to get established a Survey Archive. I went to some trouble outside to try and get research resources to enable that to happen, and the fascinating thing is, 20 years later it was being done! But a Panel Survey, etc., has developed and 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose} is ver
y much in the lead in doing that. I only wish it had been done a lot sooner, because I think that the importance of that particular work, and the way it would operate independently, because it\rquote s independence is a very cardinal issue as far as I
\rquote m concerned, might have been secured more easily at the earlier stage. But that\rquote s an interesting debate to have about the formation of a new university.
