Well, there are various figures that one could pick out from the early days, like Alan Walker, Fred Reid, Colin Low [Berit Stueland, Irene Loach, Tony Sm
ythe, Ann Shearer, Bernard Brett, James Loring]. Colin Low, in particular, who has, until recently, chaired the Disability Alliance Educational and Research Association, which is a kind of companion of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname City}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Alliance{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} campaigning group, which it star
ted as. It divided into two groups, one largely for tax purpose, may I say, as many of these Groups do; so that there is a kind of campaigning, more politicised side of it, of things that the government might object to, but things which the government cou
ldn\rquote t possibly object to, like the mere circulation of Handbooks and the provision of information to people who are disabled. So there\rquote s these two sides. And Colin has been absolutely crucial, for many years, as a blind person ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 What sort of personality has he got, then?
