ve grown in respect for, who now, I think, deserves acclaim, is Lorna Reith, who is currently the Director of the Disability Alliance, who\rquote s had enormous problems of sorting out internal problems in the last two or three years. She\rquote 
s been with the Disability Alliance for about four years, and she, through her own skills in diplomacy and in grasp of the issues, is now accepted as a k
ind of go-between in the discussions between the New Labour Government and the disability organisations, in the development of disability rights and income. And she\rquote s a very substantial person in this, and I applaud her. 
