Sally is physically quite substantially disabled, but is a live wire. She has a very loquacious manner, gets through a lot of material, is very quick on the uptake, sometimes can\rquote 
t see the wood for the trees, was a remarkably good appointment as a Director of the Child Poverty Action Group; although she\rquote s had a lot of the staff problems we\rquote 
ve been speaking of just now, of people who spent more time on sorting out the rights and wrongs of the job description applying to them, than the rights and wrongs of what the Child Poverty Action Group could do for families in poverty. She\rquote 
s had more than her fair share of those internal management problems, but has succeeded in maintaining a ve
ry high public profile. After all, the Child Poverty Action Group has a relatively minor income compared with some of the very big Departments of State, and to command such respect for both it\rquote s integrity and it\rquote 
s knowledge, as it does, is a remarkable achievement. Now, just as a final part of the story of your political involvement, I think you ought to say something about your present role as the spouse of a Member of Parliament.
