\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Peter:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
Politically! This is a necessary preliminary to explaining the political end of things. I suppose that some of the interest here is what any academic might grudgingly admit, that, from being an outsider, I feel more of an insider now. I\rquote 
ve understood more of my innocence or naivete about politics, and in a way, through Jean I\rquote ve learnt more respect for political arts. Maybe I knew about them in theory before, and I\rquote ve already indicated that I had enormous respect for peo
ple like Dick Crossman, even when I disagreed with them, they displayed some of the arts of political involvement and dexterity. But I think, also, the academic can be a bit detached from the day-to-day, blow-by-blow involvement of what\rquote 
s going on. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid3890122 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 It\rquote s almost like saying to people, \'93
Look, you may care passionately\'94, as many lay people, not only academics, may care passionately about a particular issue, and you may have, as an academic, specialised research evidence showing you that the community care s
ervices ought to do this, that, or the other, for example. Yet when you see politics close to, you begin to say that, \'93Well, you don\rquote 
t just have to judge things by the change that is needed in the service, or the results that you want to arrive at, you\rquote ve got to piece together how that is obtained in different parts of the country, as well as in theory, nationally\'94
. And you then begin to appreciate that it\rquote s easier in some places than others, obviously, that you do have to make use of some existing institutions. You\rquote re not operating with a clean slate. You can\rquote 
t just put your drawing of the community services, \'93There you are, follow that, Professor Thompson. This is what we want to do\'94. You can work towards that, you can still be guided by that structural as
piration, but you begin to learn that the putting it into place and getting it moving in that direction, is quite an art in itself, and quite a - there will be, there will be a lot of obstructions en route, provided by groups of opinion, provided by veste
d interests or by organisations which feel threatened in the process and want you to consider them as an alternative way of handling matters. And the temptations in this course are manifold. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid3890122 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 So it\rquote 
