\rquote s working, can adapt to these circumstances. It\rquote s almost like saying it\rquote s an almost impossible job to kind of fill in what is going to happen. It\rquote 
s like making a forecast, a weather forecast, not just for the next day or two. It\rquote s like saying, \'93Well, how do I arrive at July conditions in the year 1999, from October or September 1998? What could I do which might help?\'94 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid3890122 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 And it\rquote s like saying, \'93
Well, you could make a difference to global warming. You might make a difference to the fish in the sea. You might make a difference to the diesel fumes\'94. Okay, I\rquote m limited in c
onjuring up this image, but we all know that there are lots of different courses of action we could take to try to persuade the Americans to contribute better to the problem of global warming. And how that can be done. Politicians are often very well-equi
pped to vary strategies. 
