t have - you know, we talk about the New Deal and giving people training for employment, but where\rquote 
s the New Deal for aspiring Members of Parliament? Or aspiring councillors and so on. There are very serious things that politicians need to absorb, including those from academics, and we can\rquote t just leave it to chance, and say, \'93
Oh, well, if they don\rquote t take the decisions, so be it\'94. But, you see, unless you put the decisions in forms which they understand, and they are persuaded to look at more the way in which the forms of those decisions are built up
 over days and weeks and months in different areas of the country, that\rquote s partly what I\rquote m saying. 
