But we - I was swept off my feet. I found it extraordinarily difficult to try and relate this to my life in Colchester, and my work in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}. She, after all, lived in Taunton, the other end o
f England, and we agreed to keep in touch after those first three or four days at the Party Conference, and we went on fast discovering that we shared a great deal in common - like our interest in social development, social inequality. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid5648674 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 I discovered that 
she was of working-class background, in that her father was, or had been a Trade Union Organiser. His Union looked after people who made leather gloves until the late seventies, or early eighties, when no glove-making industry was left in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns3{\factoidname place}}Britain{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And he lived at Yeovil with her. She\rquote 
d left school at 16. Her mother had died at [38 years of age] of a brain tumour, so Jean looked after her father and her younger sister for the next years. In fact, I think her mother died before she was 16, 
I think it was more like 14, but she looked after her father in her teens, and her sister, and left school at 16. Then went into the Civil Service in a minor capacity, in the Inland Revenue, as far as I understand it. Had two children. Her husband crashed
 and was flying these gliding planes, what do they call them [ - hang-gliders and microlites] ...
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s22\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid11733749 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid10294858\charrsid10294858 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733749\charrsid10294858 Hang-gliding?
